      • checkForUpdate

        public void checkForUpdate()
                    throws java.net.UnknownHostException,
                           java.lang.Exception
        This method connecting to the internet, check if a new version of this application is available and shows the user if his version is up to date or not.
        if its up to date a dialog will be shown to visual the user that there is no update.
        if its NOT up to date a dialog will be shown, inform the user that there is new version to downlload and if he want to download the new version
        - if the user want to download, a new updater will fired (JFrameDownloadUpdate)
        Throws:
        java.net.UnknownHostException
        java.lang.Exception
        See Also:
        JFrameDownloadUpdate

      • checkForUpdateSilent

        public void checkForUpdateSilent()
        This method connecting to the internet, check if a new version of this application is available and shows the user if his version IS NOT up to date.
        if its up to date nothing happands.
        if its NOT up to date a dialog will be shown, inform the user that there is new version to downlload and if he want to download the new version
        - if the user want to download, a new updater will fired (JFrameDownloadUpdate)
        See Also:
        JFrameDownloadUpdate
